Bill,

    I agree that a TTL of 3600 seconds is too short (though I know
I'm using them in my database right now -- I'll fix that).

    On the more general philosophical questions,  I believe that
part of the advantage of the domain server is that new information
can be circulated fairly quickly.  I think that people should be
tailoring their servers with the idea that any change they make
to a set of RR's will be propagated to the rest of the net within
24 hours or less.

    I should point out here that my primary concern here is mail.
If my host breaks and I want to re-route its mail, my database
better be set up so that everyone will ask for MX RRs soon enough
that I won't lose any mail because someone has held it for 3 days.

Craig Partridge
CSNET Technical Staff

